<HEADLINE> FIFA Postpones Venue Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Football's international governing
body FIFA postponed the venue decision on the match between
Albania and Northern Ireland to August 12.
</P>
<P>
This qualifying match of the European Group 9 World Cup was
scheduled to be played on September 10 at Tirana, Albanian
capital.
</P>
<P>
However, the political situation in Albania put the match in
doubt. Albania's previous home matches against Germany and Ukraine
repectively were switched to Spain for the same reason.
</P>
<P>
Other three qualifying matches, Gabon v Sierra Leone, Syria v
Krygzstan and Yemen v Uzbekista, will also postponed for various
reasons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
