<HEADLINE> Fujian Industry Shows Sound Performance in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 21 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The industries at township
level and above in east China's Fujian Province contributed a
combined output value of nearly 97 billion yuan in the first half
of this year, up 17.8 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase was four percentage points higher than the
national average, and ranks the third in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the provincial statistics bureau, the growth rate
of the state-owned industries has been accelerated;
overseas-funded enterprises report a high increase in output
value; light and heavy industries have expanded simultaneously;
the export of products has continued to grow rapidly; and
industrial profits have improved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0015 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Waigaoqiao Sees Sharp Growth in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 21 (Xinhua/OANA) -- The Waigaoqiao Bonded Zone
in Shanghai's Pudong New Area has reported a sharp increase in
foreign trade in the first half of this year, with a combined
trade volume of one billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
This figure is a growth of 114 percent over the same period of
last year, according to local customs statistics.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the zone's total exports rose 81 percent, to reach
262 million dollars-worth, and its import value came to 804
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Waigaoqiao is the country's largest bonded zone, with a planned
area of 10 sq km.
</P>
<P>
The zone has always made efforts to develop its potential, and
to encourage processing industry over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors now are allowed to do any kind of business
except commercial retail.
</P>
<P>
Specialists say that the zone's rapid growth of foreign trade
might continue till the end of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
