<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanjing Bids Farewell to Welfare Housing Allocation System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 21 (Xinhua/OANA) -- This capital of east China's
Jiangsu Province has promulgated rules to put an end to the
traditional welfare housing allocation system.
</P>
<P>
The new rules stipulate that a new system will be applied to
the allocation of newly-built residences, which mainly focus
on selling publicly-owned housing property instead of renting.
</P>
<P>
Under the new rules, publicly-owned residences newly built by
government units and departments, social communities, enterprises
and institutions in the city should be sold to their staff members
in line with the housing sales policies contained in the housing
reform package.
</P>
<P>
The rules provide that units may also build houses by raising
their own funds, and these houses will be sold to their employees
at cost price upon completion.
</P>
<P>
Households with annual incomes below 50,000 yuan or average
annual per capita income less than 16,600 yuan are allowed to
apply to purchase houses at cost price.
</P>
