<HEADLINE> U.S. Company Provides Free E-mail </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Excite, Inc. of the U.S. today
introduced MailExcite, a free Web-based email service which gives
users a life-long permanent email address on the Web.
</P>
<P>
With this move, Excite merges what consumers traditionally use
on an online service with Excite's broad range of navigational
services and redefines what an online service on the Web is.
MailExcite is available immediately, without charge, at
http://www.excite.com.
</P>
<P>
Accessible through any computer connected to the Internet,
MailExcite allows users to have one email address for life even if
a user changes locations, ISPs or Internet service providers.
</P>
<P>
The user can have a private email account, whether accessed at
home, work, or through a friend's computer.
</P>
<P>
MailExcite makes it easier for business travelers who need
convenient and constant access to email, college students who
relocate quite often, professionals who change jobs but want to
consistently stay in contact with friends and family and anyone
looking for the convenience of an email address that they can keep
for life, according to the company.
</P>
<P>
Users can simply go to http://www.mailexcite.com, enter their
user name and password and immediately have access to free
Web-based email that operates similarly to other off-the-shelf
email packages. No downloading of software or installation is
necessary, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
