<HEADLINE> EU-Bosnian Tele-communication Agreement Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 21 (Xinhua) --The European Union on Monday
signed a telecommunication agreement with the Muslim-Croat
federation of Bosnia, paying the way for restoration of telephone
lines throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The Memorandum of Understanding for the Rehabilitation of the
Telecommunications Network in Bosnia and Hercegovina was signed by
Donato Chiarinl, head of the Representation Office of European
Commission in Sarajevo and Edhem Bicakcic, prime minister of the
Bosnian Federation.
</P>
<P>
Bicakcic said after the signing ceremony that the inter-entity
telecommunication link should start to functioning as early as
September.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, EU will provide, on a grant basis, Bosnia
with the equipment and training necessary for the re-establishment
of telecommunications link throughout Bosnia, including
inter-entity links between the Federation and the Republika
Srpska.
</P>
<P>
The EU will initially give eight million ECUs (about 16 million
German Marks) for the project, according a press release of the EC
office here.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnia Muslim side had previously rejected the EU project,
arguing that it will lead to three independent telecommunication
centers controlled by different ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
The restoration of telecommunications and on May 30, during an
international conference in Sintra, Portugal, participants called
on the Bosnia parties to agree to the EU proposal by mid-July or
face unspecified punishment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
