<P>
LONDON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- All shares on leading European
stock markets finished lower on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 index suffered its second consecutive sharp
decline as the latest Wall Street jitters sparked a round of
profit-taking in leading British shares. The FTSE-100 ended at
4,805.7, down 71.5 points.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, a merger of two of Germany's largest regional
commercial banks failed to keep the leading shares from tumbling
in bourse trade. The DAX-30 index closed at 4,108.40, down 88.13
points.
</P>
<P>
French shares ended slightly lower after the government
announced increases in corporate taxes to enable France to reduce
its budget deficit and qualify for the European Monetary Union.
The CAC-40 index closed at 2,874.12, down 2.57 points. 
