<HEADLINE> Ghanaian Official Stresses Traditional Medicine's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Ghanaian High Commissioner to Zimbabwe
Patrick Twumasi today urged society not to neglect traditional
healers who have a major role to play in providing health,
particularly to Africans.
</P>
<P>
In a keynote address at the on-going biannual conference of the
Social Science and Health International Conference in Harare,
Twumasi said it was important for people to realize that western
medicine had its limitations.
</P>
<P>
He called upon both medical and social scientists to further study
traditional medicine which had sometimes been effective in curing
illnesses where modern medicine had failed.
</P>
<P>
''Modern medicine must not forget that traditional healers have
been effective in psychosomatic areas. We should not neglect these
healers,'' he said. 
