<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Bans Imports of Beef from Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia said today it
has banned the imports of beef from and through Belgium to
prevent possible flow of beef infected by the mad cow disease
into the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of Saudi Ministry of Trade was quoted by the Saudi
Press Agency as saying that the decision was made after the
alleged implication of the two Belgian companies in illegal sale
of British beef which has been subject to worldwide export ban
since 1996.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the ministry was cooperating with all the
concerned authorities to prevent any possible mad cow disease
infiltration into the country.
</P>
<P>
He asked importers in the kingdom to make sure of the source
of their products.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, an Islamic country with 18 million people,
imports large amounts of beef from various parts of the world
every year.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission had earlier decided to suspend the
operating licenses of the two Belgian companies specialized in
meat exports and imports.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that more than 1,000 tonnes of British
beef had been illegally exported to the Netherlands, Egypt and
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Russia announced last Friday a ban on beef imports
from Belgium. 
</P>
</TEXT>
