<HEADLINE> Turkmenistan's Economy Down 29 Percent in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Turkmenistan's gross domestic
product dropped 29 percent in the first six months this year, and
the industrial output was down 35.2 percent, a report of the
Interfax news agency said today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the National Statistics Bureau as saying that
after a 14.7 percent decrease in the January-March period, the
industrial output plummeted by 59.5 percent in the April-June
period.
</P>
<P>
The statistics bureau attributed the sudden drop to
Turkmenistan's suspension of natural gas export in March, one of
the country's pillar industries.
</P>
<P>
In addition, last year's poor cotton output also caused a 79.3
percent drop in the country's cotton processing industry.
</P>
<P>
Turkmenistan's oil output in the first six months this year
increased 1.3 percent from the same period last year to 2.2
million tons, but the natural gas output fell 46 percent to 122
million cubic meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
