<HEADLINE> Wang Guisheng Becomes Chinese Senior Representative of JLG </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Office of the Chinese Senior
Representative of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG) held
a reception this evening to welcome Wang Guisheng as Chinese
Senior Representative.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Wang succeeded Ambassador Zhao Jihua as Chinese
Senior Representative of the JLG. Zhao has been appointed as
deputy-commissioner of the Office of the Chinese Foreign
Ministry's commissioner in the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
Wang said that he was glad to arrive at his post at a time when
 the HKSAR has been established and the "one country, two systems"
 policy is being implemented.
</P>
<P>
He said that the JLG has done a lot of work over the past dozen
 years, making great contributions to the smooth transition and
successful handover of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Now that Hong Kong has returned to the motherland and China
has resumed its exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, the task
set in the Sino-British Joint Declaration for the JLG has been
basically finished," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that according to the Joint Declaration, the JLG will
continue to operate until January 1 of 2000. In the remaining two
and a half years, the two sides will continue to hold negotiations
on issues when the necessity arises.
</P>
<P>
HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa and many local dignitaries
were present at the reception.  
</P>
</TEXT>
