<HEADLINE> Japanese Electronic Giant Quits France for China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese electronic appliances
group, the JVC, today announced that it is removing a video
recorder factory from Villiers-La Montagne in northeast France to
China.
</P>
<P>
The JVC Manufacturing France said it already has three
candidates -- two American and one Asian -- applying for taking
over the site of the factory, which is scheduled to be closed on
July 31.
</P>
<P>
The JVC will have to pay compensations for the 235 workers it
has employed, and negotiations are going on between the management
board and workers' representatives.
</P>
