<HEADLINE> US-Made Warship Goes on Auction Block </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- An old US-made warship was
auctioned off here today for 2.01 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Zhangjiagang Hongchang Salvage Company Ltd, in east China's
Jiangsu Province, became the new owner of the ship after more than
30 rounds of fierce bidding.
</P>
<P>
The ship is 100.3 m long, and has a displacement of 3,900
tons. It was first given as a gift to the Kuomintang navy after
being built in the United States in 1942. It had been in the
possession of the People's Liberation Army since 1949, until it
was decommissioned two years ago.
</P>
<P>
The landing vessel was sold in 1995 to a Shenzhen company,
which, however, was unable to pay a Shanghai shipbuilder to turn
it into a multi-function yacht, though work on major structures
had already been completed.
</P>
<P>
So the Shanghai No.1 Intermediate People's Court entrusted a
local auctioneer to put the ship up for auction, after accepting a
lawsuit from the Shanghai shipbuilder.  
</P>
</TEXT>
