<HEADLINE> Special Fund Helps Poor Ningbo Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A special fund has been created in
this coastal port city in east China's Zhejiang Province
to provide financial aid to the city's poor families.
</P>
<P>
Guo Tianfang, an official in charge of the administration of
the "Ningbo City Fund to Help Poor Workers", said the fund will be
used to help families under the city's minimum living standard.
</P>
<P>
The fund, backed by the Ningbo city government, adds up to
6.9 million yuan, if contributions from all walks of life are
taken into consideration, he said.
</P>
<P>
So far, Ningbo has issued certificates to some 200 poor
families, with which they can apply help from the fund, and also
some preferential treatment in housing, water and electricity
fees, etc.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of money from the fund, he noted, was
distributed during the lunar Spring Festival this year.
</P>
<P>
In September the city will take measures to help the children
of the needy families to complete their schooling with aid from
the fund, Guo said.  
</P>
