<HEADLINE> Blatter Confident of Ronaldo's Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- World football ruling body FIFA
general secretary Sepp Blatter is confident of an agreement
between Barcelona and Inter Milan on Brazilian international
striker Ronaldo's transfer.
</P>
<P>
Blatter said on Tuesday that the only problem was the amount of
the transfer fee. Ronaldo has paid 27.5 million U.S. dollars to
make him a free agent.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona vice-president Joan Gaspart announced an extra 17
million U.S. dollars to acknowledge the expiry of Ronaldo's
contract which should not come to an end until 2004.
</P>
<P>
However, Inter Milan announed on Tuesday that the club would
not pay a cent more than the world record 27.5 million dollar
transfer fee demanded by Ronaldo's transfer clause.
</P>
<P>
The dispute on the transfer fee forced FIFA to postpone the
scheduled talk on Tuesday between the two clubs to next week. The
decision was made on Monday at Zurich, Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
