<HEADLINE> "China's Financial Situation Stable" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua/OANA) -- China has enjoyed a smooth
financial performance in the first half of this year, through
keeping to a moderately tight money policy, further adjusting the
credit structure and flexibly wielding financial instruments.
</P>
<P>
"Relatively good outcome was seen in controlling the macro
economy, furthering financial supervision, preventing financial
risks and thereby supporting economic growth," according to a
