<HEADLINE> FIFA Sets Asian World Cup Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Football's world governing body
FIFA made the Asian final round draw for the 1998 World Cup at
Zurich Tuesday with Japan and South Korea in same group.
</P>
<P>
Japan and South Korea were drawn in Group B along with the
United Arab Emirates, Kazakstan and Uzbekstan, while Saudi Arabia,
Kuwait, China, Iran and Qatar will play in Group A.
</P>
<P>
For the draw, South Korea and Saudi Arabia were seeded in
different groups to avoid a clash between the two Asian qualifiers
for the 1994 World Cup finals in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The matches will be played on a home-and-away basis between
September 12 and November 9. Winners of the two groups qualify
directly for France.
</P>
<P>
The group runners-up will compete for third place in the Asian
Zone, and the loser of these two has another play-off against the
Oceania Zone winner Australia in November to decide which advances
to France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
