<HEADLINE> Aguta Expected Soon Recovery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Boston marathon champion Lameck
Aguta of Kenya has come to life after he was unconcious for a week
on Nairobi hospital bed, his doctor said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Aguta, who suffered head injuries in a crash as his car into a
ditch on July 12, was moved from Nairobi hospital's High
Dependency Unit on Monday to a general ward.
</P>
<P>
Doctor Patrick Akulu Okoth expected a soon recovery after the
Kenyan 10,000 meters champion was fully conscious and could move
his limbs and the rest of his body.
</P>
<P>
The doctor said Aguta had no broken limb and could leave
hospital any time from Friday after a head scan is to be fixed on
Wednesday. he is also expected to be back on his feet in about
three months after "psychiatric rehabilitation".
</P>
<P>
Aguta said from his hospital bed he would not be in Athens next
month for the world championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
