<HEADLINE> China to Host 15th World Petroleum Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The 15th World Petroleum Congress
(WPC) is scheduled to be held in Beijing between October 12 and 16
this year, with an expected attendance of about 3,000
representatives from over 80 countries and regions across the
world.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the upcoming WPC will be "Technology and
Globalization -- Leading the Petroleum Industry into the 21st
Century."
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao, chairman of the Chinese Organizing Committee of the
15th WPC, noted that the five-day conference consists of six
plenary addresses, 21 panel forums, 10 review and forecast reports
and a ministerial forum. In addition, some 95 papers will be
presented to the congress and 240 papers will be offered for
academic exchange.
</P>
<P>
All the reports and papers will focus on issues of oil
exploration, development and drilling, processing technology,
natural gas, oil and gas reserves, environmental protection and
safe production, as well as oil and gas transportation, the
chairman added.
</P>
<P>
He said that oil experts throughout the world will conduct
exchanges on the latest scientific and technological results
concerning oil production from different perspectives.
</P>
<P>
They will discuss the opportunities and challenges facing the
world petroleum industry in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, the WPC organizing committee will hold
an international exhibition on oil, gas and petrochemicals and
about 600 companies and enterprises across the world will display
their latest oil scientific and technological results, equipment
and products.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for the upcoming world petroleum congress, China set
up the Chinese organizing committee of WPC in 1993, with former
president of the China National Petroleum Corp (CNPC) Wang Tao
acting as chairman. Other members of the organizing committee are
from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the State Science and
Technology Commission, the Chinese Academy of Sciences, the
Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources, the China Petrochemical
Corp, the China National Offshore Oil Corp and the China National
Petroleum Corp.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese organizing committee, the WPC was set
up in London in 1933, with its first congress held the same
year. It now consists of 47 member states, all of which are the
world's major oil producers and consumers.
</P>
<P>
The WPC is held every three years. China joined in the WPC
organization in 1979. It is the first time for the country to host
WPC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
