<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Regional Flag Combines Wisdom of People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Qian Weichang, vice-chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), described the regional flag and
regional emblem of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) as the "crystalization of the collective wisdom."
</P>
<P>
Qian, former director of the Committee for Selecting Designs
for the Regional Flag and Regional Emblem of the Hong Kong SAR,
said the work was completed with help from the committee members
as well as members of the Drafting Committee for the Basic Law of
the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The creation of the regional flag and regional emblem was a
nationwide event, drawing entries from Chinese people both at home
and abroad.
</P>
<P>
On April 17, 1987, the fourth plenary session of the Drafting
Committee for the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR adopted a
procedure for collecting and approving the designs of the regional
flag and regional emblem of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
The Committee for Selecting Designs for the Regional Flag and
Regional Emblem of the Hong Kong SAR was also formed in July
1987. The committee consisted of 11 members, including five
members of the Drafting Committee for the Basic Law and six
experts in various fields.
</P>
<P>
During the period for receiving applications, the committee
received 7,147 designs from people all over the country and
overseas.
</P>
<P>
After a series of meetings, during which opinions were
solicited from various circles, the committee selected the three
best designs and developed three styles of the regional flag and
regional emblem which carried the pattern of the bauhinia flower.
</P>
<P>
On February 14, 1990, the Ninth Plenary Session of the Drafting
Committee for the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR passed a
procedure for selecting drafts of the regional flag and regional
emblem of the Hong Kong SAR in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Drafting Committee in the afternoon of February
16 chose one set from the three copies, with more than two-thirds
of the members voting to approve the design.
</P>
<P>
On April 4, 1990, the designs were adopted at the Third Session
of the Seventh National People's Congress along with the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Since then, a red flag and an emblem with a bauhinia
highlighted by five star-tipped stamens have become symbols of the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
