<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Developed Province Helping Needy People In Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang Province in east China
is using its capital, technology, and information in combination
with the rich resources, markets, and inexpensive labor in the
Three Gorges Dam area, to help local people improve their lives.
</P>
<P>
The province has signed more than 100 contracts worth 800
million yuan with the area and nearby Sichuan Province to help the
needy people.
</P>
<P>
It has also financed the construction of nearly 30 primary
schools in the area, which have helped thousands of drop-outs
return to school. It has helped resettle more than 4,000 migrant
farmers and provided jobs for 5,000 laborers from the two regions.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, the State asked all provinces to help the poor in the
Three Gorges area. Last year, Zhejiang was told to take charge
of poverty-eradication efforts in the area and in some poor parts
of Chongqing city and Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Hangzhou-based Wahaha Group spent 40 million yuan in 1994
setting up a branch company in Fuling city, and took on the task
of moving and reorganizing three local enterprises that were
running at a loss and which were due to be covered by the waters
of the Three Gorges.
</P>
<P>
The branch introduced a competitive system and management
methods to help revitalize the three otherwise bankrupt
businesses, providing job opportunities for 1,200 workers in the
process. In 1995, the company had 66 million yuan in output value
and more than six million yuan in pre-tax profits, a figure that is
expected to hit 40 million yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
The state's strategy, started by Deng Xiaoping, is for the more
developed East to help the undeveloped West to narrow the economic
gap and seek common prosperity, Zhang Qimei, vice-governor of
Zhejiang, explained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
