<HEADLINE> 70 Feared Killed as Bus Plunges into River in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 70 people were feared
killed when an overcrowded bus plunged into the swollen Usri river
in India's Bihar state this afternoon, the Press Trust of India
reported.
</P>
<P>
The bus was swept away by strong currents of the swollen river
while crossing a bridge, local police officer Sujata Chaturvedi
told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the bus was crowded with passengers and they
feared that at least 70 might have perished.
</P>
<P>
However, Chaturvedi said she feared that about 40 people had
been killed in the accident.
</P>
<P>
She said the ill-fated bus was yet to be traced as it might
have been swept several kilometers away by the strong currents.
Efforts were on to trace it, she added.  
</P>
