<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills 14 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 people died in sleep
and three were missing in a landslide triggered by heavy rains in
India's Kerala state late Monday night, the Press Trust of India
(PTI) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Another 18 people were injured in the tragedy which took place
in the mountainous Idukki district of the southern India state.
</P>
<P>
Police said huge mounds of earth and boulders hurtled down a
steep slope burying several settlements in the valley below and
killing the victims who were asleep.
</P>
<P>
Some of the injured were in a critical condition.
</P>
<P>
Round-the-clock rescue operations are on by police with help
from local people, PTI said.  
</P>
