<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finance Minister Calls for Better Fiscal Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Finance Minister Liu
Zhongli called here today for improved and tightened fiscal
management, while pointing out problems such as high deficits and
indebtedness.
</P>
<P>
"Ineffective fiscal management has become an evident problem in
need of an urgent solution, in spite of all the efforts the
financial departments have made in the field during the past few
years," he told a national conference on fiscal work that is in
session in this capital of northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
He said that the emphasis of the task should be on five
aspects. First, the taxation departments should enhance tax
collection, perfect taxation policies, solve problems such as tax
evasion and fraud, and halt unauthorized extension of tax
reductions and exemptions.
</P>
<P>
He also called for tighter control over fiscal spending, to
effectively check any unnecessary overspending that eats away at
fiscal revenue.
</P>
<P>
The authorities also need to have a tighter rein on the
extra-budgetary funds, the minister said, while urging a better
handling of the state assets to help them increase value rather
than drain it off.
</P>
<P>
Redoubled efforts are also necessary to better guide and
supervise Chinese accountants, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
