<HEADLINE> China Meets Wheat Purchase Quota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China has met its annual wheat
purchase quota, 10-percent more than last year, according to the
State Grain Reserve Administration.
</P>
<P>
By July 15, the state has purchased 18 billion kg of wheat from
14 major wheat producing areas, 1.6 billion kg, or 10 percent more
than for last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Of that amount, 13.7 billion kg were purchased under mandatory state
targets and 4.3 billion kg at market prices.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, Anhui, Yunnan and Shaanxi provinces have met the
state-set quotas. Other provinces are accelerating the pace of
purchases. 
</P>
