<HEADLINE> China's First Clinic for Healthy Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Capital Pediatrics Research
Institute on Monday officially launched China's first outpatient
service for children after a four-month trial run here.
</P>
<P>
The institute, located in downtown Beijing, is equipped with
advanced medical equipment, and a group of experienced doctors and
nurses, today's Beijing Youth Daily said.
</P>
<P>
Among the renowned doctors at the institute are Dr. Wu
Guangchi, Dr. Jin Yuling and Dr. Dai Yuehua, co-founder of the
facility. They are skilled in pediatric nutrition, child
psychology and genetics.
</P>
<P>
On opening day, parents and their children swarmed to the
clinic for doctors' advice in spite of the relatively costly
registration fee, 25 yuan or three US dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,400 children have been taken there for psychotherapy,
nutritional consultation, intelligence and physical development
tests and general health check-ups. 
</P>
