<HEADLINE> HK Residents Satisfied with Police Services: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Most residents here are
satisfied with the performance of the Hong Kong police forces, the
local Chinese-language daily Wen Wei Po said today.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper cited a public opinion survey to show that 72
percent of a total of 804 pollees described the quality of police
services in Hong Kong as "good" or "very good".
</P>
<P>
Some 21 percent of the pollees described it as "normal," the
paper added.
</P>
<P>
The survey, designed to provide information on how to improve
the forces' service and performance, was conducted between March
24 and April 3.
</P>
<P>
The results of the first survey of this kind, conducted last
December, showed that the Hong Kong police forces' services were
rated as good with regard to maintaining public order, controlling
traffic, and fighting against illegal immigration, narcotics
crimes, non-firearm violent crimes, vice activities, organized
crimes and firearms crimes.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether some 28,000 policemen in Hong Kong for a
population of 6.3 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
