<HEADLINE> Share Prices Remain Steady on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices remained almost
unchanged on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell a mere 0.24 points to close at 1950.51
today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume dropped to 142.84 million units, valued at
387.95 million Singapore dollars (about 267.55 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overtook advances by 165 to 150, while 313
other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
The Asia Food and Properties was the most actively traded stock
as it posted a turnover of 14.52 million units. It was followed by
Heshe Holdings which had 11.79 million shares traded. The Tianjin
Zhong Xin was next with 9.88 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Asean Fund led the gainers of day as it rose 30 cents to finish
at 16.2 US dollars. SPK-Sentosa increased 27 cents to end at 2.22
Singapore dollars, while OUE gained 25 cents to close at 6.85
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, GE Life was the biggest loser as it declined
1.4 dollars to end at 18.5 Singapore dollars. The Singapore Press
Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell 70 cents to close at 27.6 Singapore
dollars. Shell finished 34 cents lower at 4.14 dollars.  
</P>
