<HEADLINE> Thailand Closes Border with Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Thai authorities have ordered the
closure of a number of border checkpoints to stop refugee influx
following heavy fighting inside Cambodia, according to reports
here today.
</P>
<P>
The checkpoints in Ubon Ratchathai and Surin provinces in the
northeast of Thailand have been closed following fighting in
northwestern Cambodia between troops loyal to the rival co-prime
ministers. The fighting forced thousands of Cambodians to flee
toward the Thai border.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, about 30,000 Cambodians gathered at a border pass
waiting to cross into Surin province.
</P>
<P>
In Sa Kaew's Aranyaprathet District, the border situation was
still tense, and about 10,000 Cambodians had gathered at the
village opposite Sa Kaew, preparing to cross the border into
Thailand if fighting intensified, said reports reaching here.
</P>
