<HEADLINE> Market Prices Remain Stable in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Market prices across China
remained stable in June, and the commodity retail price index and
the resident consumption price index rose 0.8 percent and 2.8
percent from the same month in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the State Planning Commission show that both
the general retail price index and the resident consumption price
index were down by 1.7 percent from May, due to the seasonal drops
in fresh vegetable and fruit prices.
</P>
<P>
According to the same source, in the first half of this year,
the price increase range for retail sales and resident consumption
rose by 1.8 percent and 4.1 percent, respectively, over the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The commission also urged different localities to carry out the
policy on buying any amount of grain at protective prices
from the farmers 
</P>
