<HEADLINE> Thai Police to Crack Down on Foreign Criminals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Thai immigration police are to
step up their efforts to prevent foreign criminals from entering
the country, the Bangkok Post reported today
</P>
<P>
With assistance from the Interpol (international police), the
Immigration Police Bureau of Thailand will prevent criminals from
South Asia from using Thailand as a gateway for sending foreign
unskilled labor to third countries, bureau Deputy Commissioner Pol
Maj-Gen Chalermdej Chompoonuch was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Interpol has agreed to give Thai police information about
criminals blacklisted by the United States and by European and
Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
To prevent South Asian gangsters from sending foreign labor to
third countries through Thailand, Thai authorities will issue
visas only for those with round-trip air tickets.  
</P>
