<HEADLINE> South China Economic Zone Helps Hong Kong Train Professionals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to China's reforms and
opening-up, Shenzhen, China's first special economic zone, is not
only a prominent economic success story but an increasingly
important training center for its next-door neighbor Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
As a pioneer in China's reforms, Shenzhen in Guangdong Province
has plenty of well-educated professionals and advanced technology,
while Hong Kong, although a major international trade and
financial center, lacks technical personnel.
</P>
<P>
So, in recent years, Shenzhen has held a number of training
courses for Hong Kong people, covering everything from nursing to
CAD computers and domestic market operations.
</P>
<P>
With its return to the mainland, it and Shenzhen have come to
be even closer economically, so co-operation in training is
expected to increase.
</P>
<P>
Recently, experts from both sides held a series of meetings to
discuss the possibilities and ways to improve exchanges. A
proposal was made to set up universities and special training
centers in Shenzhen to provide skilled personnel for Hong
Kong-based companies.
</P>
<P>
Some local experts say that Shenzhen's multitude of
professionals need greater international expertise, while Hong
Kong wants more scientists and technicians with a better
knowledge of the basic sciences and technology, especially in
hi-tech fields. 
</P>
