<HEADLINE> Chongqing's Industry Up In First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, China's newest
municipality, scored high economic growth in the first half of the
year, with its industrial output totaling 39.4 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Added value of these enterprises was 11.7 billion yuan during
that period, 6.2 billion of that from large and medium-sized
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Automobiles are still the pillar of industrial growth in the
city, largely because of the emphasis placed by the municipal
government on the sector.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, 84,100 automobiles had been built, up 54.2
percent year-on-year. Of that number, 60,000 were produced by the
Chang'an Automobile Co. Ltd., a large state company, worth 1.4
billion yuan in sales.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing's industrial growth in the first half was
characterized by development in diverse sectors. Added value of
state-owned enterprises shot up 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Joint-stock companies, collectively-owned businesses and
Sino-foreign joint ventures registered a nearly 20 percent
increase in their added value.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, accumulated losses in Chongqing's
industrial sector shrank some 39.5 percent compared with the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government has also transferred control of some
276 small and medium-sized enterprises to lower-level
administrative offices to improve competitiveness of such
enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
