<HEADLINE> Southwest China's Rapid Growth In Ethnic Minority Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The ethnic minority areas of
southwest China's Sichuan Province have scored rapid economic and
social development, with the growth rate exceeding the province's
average for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The province has 53 ethnic groups, with a population accounting
for about seven percent of the province's total, living in compact
communities on 62 percent of the province's land mass.
</P>
<P>
Since 1990, the major economic indexes of the province's ethnic
minority areas, such as GDP, revenues, and net incomes, have all
grown. Their GDP increased by 10 percent last year and the overall
grain output increased nearly three percent.
</P>
<P>
Elementary education is universal in 80 percent of the ethnic
minority counties, and 60 percent of the counties have eradicated
illiteracy among youngsters. Nearly 90 percent of the school-age
children received an education last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has nearly 100,000 officials
belonging to ethnic groups.  
</P>
</TEXT>
