<HEADLINE> Booming Sino-Russian Border Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Suifenhe, a border
city in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, and Russia surged
185 percent to more than 170 million US dollars in the first half
of this year, a local trade official said today.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounted for more than half of Heilongjiang's total
import and exports, said Guo Xiaohua, a Suifenhe City government
official.
</P>
<P>
As one of the two largest ports of entry for railway transport
on the Sino-Russian border, Suifenhe takes up an important position
in economic and trade development between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
It can receive 1.5 million visitors and deals with six million
tons of cargo by rail and truck each year. The city has also
opened mobile phone, optical fiber, and direct-dial
telecommunications services, and improved infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
To boost trade, the local government has opened 40 specialty
stores and built fairly complete information, science and
technology, capital, and technical personnel exchange systems.
</P>
