<HEADLINE> China Records 9.5 Percent Half-Year Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China maintained a rapid economic
growth while keeping inflation low in the first half of this year,
the State Statistics Bureau (SSB) said here today.
</P>
<P>
Gross Domestic Product totaled 3,318 billion yuan in the past
six months, an increase of 9.5 percent over the same period of
last year, SSB spokesman Ye Zhen told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
The retail price index, an indicator for price rises in goods,
rose 1.8 percent and the consumer price index, which measures
price rises in both goods and services, went up by 4.1 percent, Ye
said.
</P>
<P>
Fixed-asset investment chalked up an increase of 13.5 percent
to reach 741.7 billion yuan during the period.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural production was further boosted with output of
summer grains hitting a record high of 123.95 million tons, 10.75
million tons more than last year, Ye said. 
