<HEADLINE> Number of Rail Passengers In China Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's railways carried a total of
2.22 million passengers last month, including 534,000
long-distance travelers, up 25 percent from the same period of
last year, according to the Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
This is a considerable increase after years of sluggish rail
transport business. In the past few years, more people have turned
to automobiles or air transport for faster or more comfortable
service.
</P>
<P>
Railways moved 78,100 rail cars of cargo in June, 100 more than
were scheduled, including 31,380 cars of coal. They also surpassed
transport targets for oil, timber, minerals, cement, fertilizer,
pesticides, and grain last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
