<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jetta Car Sales Up Dramatically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The No.1 Automobile and
Volkswagen Corporation in Changchun, northeast China's Jilin
Province, sold 20,100 Jetta cars in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
This is a 101.7 percent rise over the same period last
year. According to sources at the Sino-German joint venture,
20,600 Jettas were produced in the same period, up 45 percent from
last year.
</P>
<P>
Jetta's domestic market share rose to 8.3 percent in the first
quarter of the year and to 9.1 percent by the end of June,
compared to only 6.7 percent at the end of 1996. It is expected to
go up to 10 percent by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The company is reporting a profit also for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The No.1 Automobile and Volkswagen Corporation has China's
first modern assembly line, with a production capacity of 150,000
cars a year. The assembly line was completed last year when the
auto market was recovering after a more than a three-year slump,
during which time it was losing money.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that moves to increase the variety of autos and the
use of sales agents, which were started last year, have been key
factors in promoting growth.
</P>
<P>
The company now produces Audi sedans and three types of Jettas,
and now offers more color choices. It employs more than 150 sales
agents in 30 provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions,
helping to ensure more even distribution of Jettas across the
country.
</P>
<P>
It has also improved after-sales service and has more than 150
service centers across the country, something that has helped win
more customers for the auto maker. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
