<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Company Uses New Tech to Recycle Toxic Waste </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Italian environment and land company
SIAT is hoping to use its new recycling technology to cash in on
the thousands of tons of toxic waste generated by used television
tubes, computers and neon lights.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Italy generated 56,000 tons of used tubes and 32,000
tons of electronic equipment.
</P>
<P>
These used goods, which contain cadmium, mercury and other
heavy metals, usually pollute the environment after they are
abandoned.
</P>
<P>
The technology developed by the company sucks out the heavy
metals contained in the used goods and enables them to be
reused. Even glass can be recycled.
</P>
<P>
The items which can't be recycled and are finally discarded
account for only six percent of the total weight of the original
product.
</P>
<P>
Last year, SIAT handled just 174 tons of used TV tubes and 719
tons of electronics equipment, a tiny fraction of the total
dumped. This year, it's hoping for a bigger share of the market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970722.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovakia Resumes Import Duties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Just seven months after abolishing
import tariffs, Slovakia today reimposed across the board import
duties in the face of a rising trade deficit.
</P>
<P>
Imports will now face tariffs of 7 percent in a move the
government said was taken to protect the national market.
</P>
<P>
Since tariffs were abolished on January 1 this year, the
country has witnessed a surge in imports which have seriously
affected domestic producers.
</P>
<P>
It also contributed to a widening trade deficit which is
expected to exceed last year's 74.5 billion koruna (about 2.4
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Slovakia took initial measures to try to curb imports in April
with limits on imports of non-alcoholic drinks, followed by limits
on imported beer in June.
</P>
<P>
But the new import tariffs have angered the neighboring Czech
Republic which has threatened to retaliate.
</P>
<P>
Slovakia and the Czech Republic emerged from the former
Czechoslovakia in 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
