<HEADLINE> China Unveils Roster for Athletics Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China on Monday announced its
27-member delegation for the World Athletics Championships with
medal hopes focused on three or four events.
</P>
<P>
As Olympic champion Wang Junxia absent from the team, China
will be well satisfied with a silver or bronze medal through Huang
Zhihong, former Olympic and world women's shotput winner, sources
from the Chinese delegation said.
</P>
<P>
Other medal hopefuls include Gao Hongmiao, last year's World
Cup women's 10-kilometer walk gold medalist and Ren Xiujuan who
currently ranked 9th in the women's triple jump.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team features both veterans and newcomers in a
preparation for the 1998 Bangkok Asian Games and the 2000 Sydney
Olympic Games, including six entries who joined in the world's top
10 of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese men athletes will compete in the 110m hurdles, long
jump, triple jump, discus throw, 20km and 50km walk while their
women compatriots will show up in the events of 100m, 200m, 4x100m
relay, 5,000m, 10,000m, 10-km walk, triple jump, shot put and
discus throw.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will leave for Athens on July 27 for the 10-day
biennial athletics gala slated from August 1. 
