<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sub-Zero Temperatures Kill 22 in Southern Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Extremely cold weather conditions
have killed at least 22 people in the Andean areas of southern
Peru since May, newspaper reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The last 3 fatalities, including 2 children, occurred in
Cailloma and Caraveli of the Arequipa department, regional health
director Gustavo Rondon Fudinaga was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
There, the temperature was down to minus 15 degrees Celsius,
and local clinics cited exposure to the cold weather as the cause
leading to the recent deaths.
</P>
<P>
In other parts of southern Argentina, such as in the department
of Puno, minus 20 degrees have been recorded.
</P>
<P>
As doctors and nurses in these areas were trained to deal with
the high incidences of cold and bronco-pneumonia, Rondon said,
authorities were striving to prevent respiratory infections.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
