time, will replace the former Hong Kong and Singapore personnel
starting this week.
</P>
<P>
The interpreters, who are required speak both English and
standard Chinese fluently, are believed to offer better service to
Chinese passengers who now account for more than half of the total
number of passengers.
</P>
