<HEADLINE> Caravan to Tour Thailand, China to Boost Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 22 (Xinhua) -- A caravan of 15 vehicles will
travel from Thailand to China's southwestern Yunnan Province via
Laos on August 3-13 in a campaign to boost tourism.
</P>
<P>
The caravan of four-wheel-drive vehicles will set out in
Bangkok, then travel to Nan province in northern Thailand. It will
finally get to Jinghong town in southern Yunnan and the province's
capital Kunming through Oudomsay of Laos,
</P>
<P>
