<HEADLINE> Argentina's Public Sector Owes 2 Million Dollars in 6 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's public sector was
running a deficit equivalent to a little over 2.0 billion
U.S. dollars in the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The six-month deficit, Finance Minister Pablo Guidotti said
today, was nearly 289 million dollars less than the goal agreed
upon with the International Monetary Fund (IMF).
</P>
<P>
