Washington D.C., the United States, set the half-year goal as 3.0
billion dollars and the annual goal as 4.5 billion.
</P>
<P>
The improved financial status of the country's public sector,
Guidotti said, should be attributed to greater economic activity,
better tax collection and more control over spending.
</P>
<P>
An IMF mission will visit Argentina in mid-August to finalize
an extended credit agreement, he said.
</P>
<P>
On its part, the Argentine government has promised to better
plan the national budget, draw up new legislations to strengthen
credit relations and improve the execution of guarantees. 
