<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Juventus Aims to Retain Top Forms with Strong Will </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Juventus coach Marcello Lippi
insisted that willpower will help his champions to stay atop of
Italian football next season.
</P>
<P>
Juventus were busy running between their Turin home and a
training base in northern Italy this week, to tune up for their
title defence and a revenge in the European Cup which they lost to
Borussia Dortmund.
</P>
<P>
With the absence of both Christian Vieri and Alen Boksic, Lippi
has spinned his hope in strikers with ball skills by recruiting
Filippo Inzaghi, top scorer last season with Atalanta.
</P>
<P>
Inzaghi is expected to play with Del Piero and newcomer Daniel
Fonseca, the Uruguayan who became strong under Lippi at Napoli in
1993-94 but performed poor after joining AS Roma.
</P>
<P>
Juventus also signed Napoli midfielder Fabio Pecchia to replace
Vladimir Jugovic, although a bigger influence will be effected by
the return of skipper Antonio Conte.
</P>
<P>
Conte injured cruciate ligaments last October in a World Cup
qualifier against Georgia. 
</P>
