<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singaporean, U.S. Navies In Annual Bilateral Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Singaporean and U.S. Navies
Monday started to conduct a bilateral exercise program code-named
Cooperation Afloat Readiness and Training (CARAT) 97.
</P>
<P>
The CARAT was introduced in 1995 on the request of the US
Seventh Fleet to conduct naval exercises with Southeast Asian
countries.
</P>
<P>
The current exercise with the Singaporean navy is scheduled to
end on August 1, the Singapore Defense Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Ten ships, one submarine, Maritime Patrol Aircraft are taking
part in various aspects of the CARAT 97 program which involves 900
U.S. and 350 Singapoean Naval personnel.
</P>
<P>
The Republic of Singapore Air Force (RSAF) and the U.S. Air
Force (USAF) are supporting the exercise with RSAF E-2C, F-5 and
A4 aircraft and USAF F-16 fighters.
</P>
<P>
The main activities planned for the war game include
multi-threat encounter exercises, anti-submarine exercises, drone
target shoots and rescue exercises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
