 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- National fiscal revenue from January to June amounted to
390.1 billion yuan, 29.9 percent more than the first half of last
year. But the expenditure in some areas outraced revenue. The
Finance Ministry called for serious attention to the imbalance.
</P>
<P>
--China is drafting the law governing people's meditation
work. Meditation is an important method of resolving civil dispute
without going to court. To date there are more than one million
meditation organizations across the country.
</P>
<P>
--The provincial government of Shanxi will allocate a special
budget of eight million yuan to help reduce local birth defects. The
target is that the incidence rate drop to half of that for the
year 1996 by the year 2,000.
