<HEADLINE> Argentine Industrial Output Rises 7.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's industrial output
reported a growth of 7.2 percent during the first half of this
year compared with the same period last year, said Argentina's
School of Business today.
</P>
<P>
The most dynamic sectors were automobile, cement, oil and food.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output in June increased 8 percent compared with
that of the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
As a whole, the industries operated at about 80 percent of
installed capacity, which was above that recorded a year ago, but
slightly below that of May 1997.
</P>
<P>
The figures prove that the industrial sector is still in a
phase of growth. 
</P>
