<HEADLINE> Russian Joins List of Expulsions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian cyclist Alexandre
Gonchentkov was thrown out of the Tour de France here on Monday
for breaking three race rules.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Gonchentkov, who won a stage of the 1996 Tour
of Italy, was found guilty of hanging onto his Roslotto team car
after 114km, taking an unscheduled refreshment stop after 92km and
for staying behind his team car for more than the permitted time
after 96km of the 208.5km 15th stage.
</P>
<P>
The decision took the total number of riders expelled to an
unprecedented four for the Tour.
</P>
<P>
The other three are Belgian national champion Tom Steels,
three-time green jersey winner Djamolodine Abdujaparov and
Gonchentkov's teammate Gerard Rue Chris Boardman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
