<HEADLINE> Lewis Lined up to Face Golota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- World Boxing Council (WBC)
heavyweight champion Lennox Lewis is being lined up to defend his
title against Poland's Andrew Golota in Las Vegas on October 4.
</P>
<P>
Golota, based in the United States, had been notorious for his
fights against Riddick Bowe for being twice disqualified because
of persistent low blows.
</P>
<P>
Lewis's last two fights have seen little fighting at all.
</P>
<P>
His first challenger, fellow Briton Henry Akinwande, was
disqualified for holding during their Lake Tahoe bout two weeks
ago.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in February, the Briton faced Oliver McCall in Las
Vegas for the vacant WBC title with the fight also turning into
fiasco in which McCall broke down in tears and refused to
fight. 
