<HEADLINE> FIFA Puts off Decision on Ronaldo Transfer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- FIFA puts off a decision on
Ronaldo's disputed transfer from Barcelona to Inter Milan, saying
the two clubs should work out an agreement between themselves.
</P>
<P>
FIFA announced in a statement on Monday that its Players'
Status Committee would not make a ruling on the issue as scheduled
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"FIFA is of the opinion that the two clubs could possibly reach
agreement," the statement said, "The Bureau for the Players'
Status Committee ... will therefore only examine the file and will
not take a formal decision on the matter..."
</P>
<P>
The two clubs, failing to reach a deal on the Brazilian's
record 27 million-dollar transfer after more than four hours' talk
on Monday, have agreed with FIFA to meet in Zurich again next week
to try to settle the case once and for all. 
</P>
</TEXT>
