<HEADLINE> UNDP Focuses Program on Poverty in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) is targeting poverty in China's western
provinces as its top development priority, according to UNDP Flash
released here today.
</P>
<P>
Arthur Holcombe, UNDP resident representative in Beijing, said
here recently that 40 percent of the UNDP's program in China for
1996-2001 is focused on poverty, according to the UNDP Flash.
</P>
<P>
UNDP funding for the new country program will be 110-120
million dollars, and that amount could double with other funding
from the Global Environment Facility, the Montreal Protocol and
cost-sharing.
</P>
<P>
In poor communities, micro-finance and income-generating
activities are being supported, and health and social services
strengthened. Other chief areas of UNDP assistance are
environmental protection and economic reform, according to the
UNDP publication. 
</P>
</TEXT>
