<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
struggled higher today, but stocks were mostly lower in nervous
trading before Tuesday's congressional testimony by Federal
Reserve chairman Alan Greenspan.
</P>
<P>
The Dow gained 16.26 points to 7,906.72, after erasing an early
50-point deficit. The blue-chip barometer hit 8,000 for the first
time last Wednesday, but then lost 150 points over the next two
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broad-market indicators slumped for the third consecutive
session, led by the technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by more than a 2-to-1
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 459.49
million shares, down from 585.61 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 2.32 to 912.98, and
the NYSE composite index fell 1.47 to 474.50.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 12.25 to 1,535.74, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 3.19 to 630.40.
</P>
<P>
The market plunged after Greenspan's last testimony in December.
</P>
</TEXT>
