<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Asks Hun Sen to Accept ASEAN Mediation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The United States, expressing
regret at Cambodia's Second Prime Minister Hun Sen's refusal of
international mediation for the recent Cambodia crisis, today
called on him to reconsider the offer.
</P>
<P>
"The United States very much regrets Hun Sen's rejection of
ASEAN (the Association of Southeast Asia Nations) mediation,"
State Department spokesman Nicholas Burns said at a briefing
today. "We hope very much he will reconsider the constructive
recommendations."
</P>
<P>
Three ASEAN foreign ministers, assigned by the organization,
went to Phnom Penh, capital of Cambodia, Saturday and offered to
broker a settlement of the crisis, erupted after Hun Sen ousted
First Prime Minister Norodom Ranariddh on July 6. But Hun Sen
flatly rejected the offer.
</P>
<P>
The United States also sent Stephen Solarz as a special envoy
to Asia Saturday on a mission of resolving the crisis by
consulting with Asian leaders, including Hun Sen. He is also
scheduled to meet Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He will brief Secretary of State Madeleine Albright on his
talks with these leaders on July 26 in Kuala Lumpur, where the
ASEAN member countries will hold a foreign ministers meeting to
discuss the situation in Cambodia. Albright is to attend the
gathering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
